The paper deals with the Unique Games problem, which is a well-studied problem in computational complexity theory and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves analyzing the properties of expanders and their Laplacian eigenvalues, which are topics in graph theory and spectral graph theory, respectively. Therefore, the paper could also be categorized under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
